But that was my *point*.  I *cannot* see a Powell Administration doing
the same things the Clinton Administration did.  He's not beholden to
the same politics, the same hang-ups that Clinton was, nor does he
have the same advisors.

My point was that Powell would probably push to run a Gulf War styled
operation:  combined arms.  An air campaign followed by a ground
campaign.  He's not a McPeak-styled &quot;Air Power Can Do Everything&quot; type
so the kind of ground campaign planning that Clinton took off the
table from Day One until about a week before the war ended wouldn't
happen.  It would be more organically inclusive.

I cannot see a Kosovo War ending the way it did in OTL, with a semi-
ambiguous result (that is:  sure Kosovo isn't de facto Serbian any
more...but what exactly *is* it's legal status?  And what is to come
next for both peoples?) masquerading as a victory.  No, Powell's not
going to stick himself or his successor with something like that.  It
goes against his own doctrinal thinking.  He'd plan to go in there,
rip Kosovo out and, just perhaps, knock out Milosevic's regime to
boot.  If the man really *is* the second coming of Hitler--as some of
the rhetoric seemed to indicate at the time--then I cannot see him
being treated as anything less.  Total victory, with a Belgrade
capitulation or forcible regime change.

But even with this more robust *Kosovo War, you're still going to have
troops in the region in 2004, if only to prevent flare-ups.  Depending
on the exact details of the Serbian thumping, said troops might be
simply canaries in a coal mine, deployed along the border with Serbia-
proper...or it might scale all the way up to a Post-WWII German/
Japanese-styled occupation force in Serbia, designed to rebuild the
country from the ground-up.

*That* was my point.  No dithering, no half-measures, no policy-by-way-
of-fear-of-Vietnam-Syndrome, no subtle clashes between the White House
and the Pentagon because the Pentagon doesn't trust the President to
do what's right...*nothing* like that is likely to occur in a Powell
White House.

